      short-description: OGNL expression construction from user-controlled input
      full-description: |-
        OGNL injection occurs when untrusted input reaches OGNL evaluation APIs
        (`Ognl.getValue(...)`, Struts OGNL utility/value-stack evaluation methods).

        Vulnerable example:

        ```java
        import ognl.Ognl;
        import ognl.OgnlContext;

        public class OgnlService {
            public Object eval(String exprFromRequest) throws Exception {
                OgnlContext ctx = new OgnlContext();
                return Ognl.getValue(exprFromRequest, ctx, ctx.getRoot()); // VULNERABLE
            }
        }
        ```

        Safe example:

        ```java
        public class OgnlService {
            public Object dispatch(String actionFromRequest, UserService userService) {
                if ("profile".equals(actionFromRequest)) {
                    return userService.currentProfile();
                }
                if ("list".equals(actionFromRequest)) {
                    return userService.listUsers();
                }
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("Unsupported action");
            }
        }
        ```

        Key vulnerable patterns covered by this rule include OGNL direct evaluators and Struts OGNL helpers
        when tainted expression text is evaluated.
